Senior Information Security Engineer, Incident Response - Carvana - January 2022

Engineer, implement and administer security tools across the enterprise. 
-- > Learn about the security tools used on daily basis and check if any prior trainings required?

Provide subject matter expertise to drive security incidents to resolution. 
--> Talk about what types of security incidents occured in past and what needs immediate focus ?

Develop, document and execute different Incident response playbooks. 
--> Learn about any exisiting playbook in place and process to document runbook.

Serve as a point of escalation to all information security incidents, that includes but not limited to providing direction, training, and guidance to other security engineers and analysts.
--> Existing policies in place and plan to address teams growth.

Conduct network and systems forensics, log analysis and basic malware analysis.
--> Existing Cyber Security Framework and Standards in Use.

Implement various information security controls to accomplish full incident containment, and mitigation.
--> Approach taken and automation scope for identification, assessment, containment and remeditaion and/or mitigation.

Drive post mortem plans to improve Carvana’s cyber security posture.
--> Existing maturity model and future scope ?

Assist in creation well-defined, time-lined, and clear deliverables.
--> Understand Overall working Process and expectation in deliverables

Work with global network engineers, systems administrators, and applications owners to implement security controls and processes.
--> CAB process and change management process

Lead different security operations projects, including process and Playbooks improvement.
--> Custom tools and methodology used to drive security program.

Build scripts, tools, or methodologies to enhance Carvana’s incident investigation processes.
--> Version control tools and external resource help 

Incident response, 
Threat detection at scale, 
Threat hunting,
creating effective infosec best practices.

TCP/IP, 
attack models ( such as MITRE’s ATT& CK framework), application at scale.
creating detection correlation rules, 
basic integration, 
deploying various InfoSec tools, 
and intelligence gathering.
Incident response, and containment practices.
Advanced understanding of cloud environments (such as AWS).
AWS cloud platform’s information security related capabilities.
A broad base of technical knowledge in system administration, network engineering, and compliance.
Proven track record of delivery results in an enterprise environment.

authentication methods, Kerberos, SAML, OAuth, etc...
G-Suite and Google security features.
internet security issues and the threat landscape.
network vulnerability scanning techniques and nmap.
host-based information security technologies such as Tanium and Crowdstrike.
security implications involving a variety of technologies including but not limited to; Microsoft, Cisco, Palo Alto security devices, Unix/Linux, Nutanix, and other market leaders in technology solutions, including mobile devices.
IDS/IPS, firewalls, proxies, and other network security technologies.


Senior Information Security Engineer - eBay - January 2022

Job Description:
Senior software developer with engineering experience working on Security attacks reduction through foundational product security fixes
Securing Customer Security accounts from various Security attack vectors like Phishing, Malware and Fraud related attacks.
Experience with working in the Security / Risk / Fraud space to build end-end security solutions to reduce monetary losses due to security loopholes and fraud
Ability to conduct deep dive investigations into Security / Fraud / Risk abuse patterns in the product code
Experience working with Big Data systems and Data analysis techniques is preferred
Knowledge of integration of Security automation solutions with systems like GitHub and Open Source Security solutions is a plus
This role will require a focus on fixing the foundational security and risk gaps in eBay Applications
Preferred Requirements:
BSCS degree or an MS degree with appropriate years of experience; We prefer 6-8 years of hands on experience.
Implementation experience with Security Malware and Phishing prevention solutions is highly preferred.
A deep understanding on existing phishing risk mitigation solutions is required.
Good understanding of OWASP top 10 vulnerabilities as it relates to secure product development
Experience on developing product solutions seeking to minimize Security attacks and fraud in monetary transactions required
Hands-on product development experience with web applications is required; some experience in application security space will be nice-to-have.
Strong development experience in Java and Node.js, and familiarity with databases (MongoDB or Hadoop) is required. Knowledge of other technologies like PHP, Python, Content management systems is a plus.
Working experience with product development teams in a continuous delivery developer role is highly desirable.
Should be able to deep dive into existing code to detect and remediate security flaws.
Self-starter and Effective communicator with the ability to work in a fast-paced environment and with a highly motivated team of top-level security specialists
